Lemony Spaghetti with Garlic and Pine Nuts for one
  --America's Test Kitchen
  
2 garlic cloves, minced
2 tbsp oil, divided
2 c chicken or vegetable broth
3 oz spaghetti
1/8 tsp red pepper flakes
1/4 c chopped fresh basil or parsley
2 tbsp Parmesan cheese, grated
2 tbsp toasted pine nuts
1/2 tsp grated lemon zest plus 2 tsp juice

Cook garlic and 1 tbsp oil in 12" nonstick skillet over low heat, stirring frequently, until garlic is pale golden brown, 7-10 min. Stir in broth, spaghetti, and pepper flakes and bring to boil. Cover and simmer vigorously over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until pasta is nearly tender, ~10 min. Uncover and continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thickened slightly, 3-6 min. Off heat, stir in remaining 1 tbsp oil, basil, Parmesan, pine nuts, and lemon zest and juice. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Serve.



Notes: can use any shape pasta, cooking times may vary
